The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Timeout

 art

 Till August 12 at Vedic Village, Rajarhat; 10 am - 6 pm: An art workshop, hosted by Artists Circle, in support of providing medical insurance coverage and medical benefit for artists. 

 Till August 14 at Academy of Fine Arts, Central Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: Paintings by Maitreyee Chatterjee. 

 Till August 14 at Academy of Fine Arts, New South Gallery; 3 pm - 8 pm: Paintings and sculptures by Sajal Kanti Mitra and Madan Gopal Dutta. 

 Till September 3 at Idiyas Gallery, 15 Dover Road; 10.30 am - 7.30 pm: Autumn Bloom, showcasing works of well-known artists. 

 PERFORMING ARTS

 August 12 at Rabindra Sadan; 5.30 pm: In aid of various developmental projects for women and children, Karma Kutir presents an evening of Rabindrasangeet and other Bengali songs featuring Manisha Murali Nair, Manoj Murali Nair, Srikanta Acharya and Bhoomi band. 

 August 12 at The Bengal Club, Salon 175; 7.30 pm: Rabindranather Chhobi O Gaan ? To commemorate Baishe Shrabon, Bengal Club presents a selection of Tagore?s paintings and songs. The programme is strung together by Prof. Sovon Som and the songs are rendered by Dr Sugata Sen. 

 DRAMA

 August 12 at Tapan Theatre; 6.30 pm: Natyargha presents its latest play, Nidhiramer Pala. Direction: Pulak Lahiri. 

 August 12 at Sisir Mancha; 6.30 pm: Sangram Guha?s two one-act plays, 16mm and Operation Flush. Produced by Bharatiya Gana Natya Sangha. 

 August 12 - 15 at Sree Thyagaraja Hall; 6.30 pm: Rasika Ranjana Sabha?s pre-diamond jubilee celebrations feature a festival of Tamil plays presented by Mahalakshmi Ladies Drama Group, Chennai. August 12: Abhinaya. August 13: Nallathor Veenai Seithey. August 14: Nan Enna Seiyyattum? August 15: Ellai Illatha Illaram. Direction: Bombay Gnanam. 

 August 12 at Sujata Sadan; 6.45 pm: Srijak presents Bechara Penchara. 

 EXHIBITION

 Till August 12 at Calcutta Information Centre exhibition gallery; 2 pm - 8 pm: Hey Mahamaran, Hey Mahajeeban ? an exhibition on Tagore. 

 August 12 at Kaushik Hall of Nari Seva Sangha, Jodhpur Park; 6 pm: Inauguration of an exclusive exhibition of Sudatta?s boutique. Raja Sen, Aninda Sarkar, Locket Chatterjee and Sonali Chowdhury will be present for the opening ceremony. The exhibition continues till August 14; 11 am -8 pm. 

 Till August 15 at Artisana, 13 Chowringhee Terrace; 11 am - 7 pm: Crafts Council of West Bengal and Sravasti present Thakurbarir Poshak, an exhibition to promote craft skills and textiles in styles developed by the Tagores. 

 Till August 13 at 8/2 Loudon Street: Earthy Myths exhibits glamorous day and evening bags in casual and formal look. 

 August 13 - 21 at Aakriti, City Centre, Salt Lake; 11 am - 9 pm: Nimble Fingers, in association with NGO store Aakriti, is organising an exhibition of Bengal?s handicraft products including handcrafted terracotta, hand-made paper stationeries and masks, buffalo horn craft, dokra, and cotton embroidery and applique. 

 PHOTOGRAPHS

 Till August 13 at Gallery Kanishka?s; 11 am - 8 pm: Freeze Frame ? an exhibition of photographs taken by lensmen of newspapers and magazines. 

 Till August 26 (Monday to Friday) at Stills Archive of Roopkala Kendro, Block GM, Sector V, Salt Lake; 12 noon - 6 pm: An exhibition titled Pather Panchali from Parimal Ray?s collection. 

 DISCUSSION

 August 12 at Bangla Academy Sabhaghar; 6.15 pm: Flor-N-Fon organises a deliberation on extinction of tiger at Sariska and its crisis in the woodlands of India. Speakers: Arin Ghosh, Atanu Raha, Ujjal Bhattacharya, Dr J.R.B. Alfred, Pranabesh Sanyal and Subimol Roy. 

 BOOK LAUNCH

 August 12 at Centre Point, 28/2 Shakespeare Sarani; 6.30 pm: Penguin Books India and Cocoon host the launch of Tin Fish authored by Sudeep Chakravarti. 

 ORATION

 August 12 at the Seminarium of the Management Centre for Human Values, IIMC Joka; 3 pm: Professor Sugata Bose will deliver ?Sri Aurobindo Memorial Oration? on The Spirit and Form of an Ethical Polity: A Meditation on Aurobindo?s Thought. 

 TALK

 August 12 at Bharatiya Bhasha Parishad; 5 pm: Dr Prakash Mangalasseri will speak in English on Ayurveda ? an alternative treatment for lifestyle ailments. 

 August 12 at Sanskrit Sahitya Parishat, 168/1 Raja Dinendra St; 5 pm: Dhirendranath Banerjee will deliver Pandit Herambanath Chatterjee Sastri Commemorative Lecture on Religion and the modern world. 

 August 12 at Ramakrishna Mission Institute of Culture, Shivananda Hall; 6 pm: Samiran Chandra Chakraborty will speak in Bengali on Veda Parikrama. 

 LECTURE

 August 13 at Netaji Bhawan, 38/2 Elgin Road; 6 pm: Prof. Eunan O?Halpin, professor of history, Trinity College, Dublin, Ireland, will deliver Sisir Kumar Bose Lecture 2005 on Assassination in Defence of Empire: Subhas Chandra Bose and British Intelligence, 1939-1945. Prof. Sugata Bose, Gardiner Professor of History, Harvard University, will be in the chair. 

 IKEBANA

 August 13 - 18 at Oxford Bookstore (Aug. 13, 5 pm), ITC Sonar Bangla (Aug. 14, 4 pm), and Calcutta Information Centre (Aug. 17, 6 pm amp; Aug. 18, 10.30 am): A unique event of Japanese style of flower araangement, conducted by Prof. Takashi Moribe, an exponent from Ikenobo Institute of Arts, Kyoto, Japan. 

